== 其他应用 ==

* 动物形象的服装从[[史前時代|史前時代]]就是人类[[文化|文化]]的一部分。有一些传统，如在[[斯诺文尼亚|斯诺文尼亚]][[普图伊|普图伊]]市的“{{link-en|Kurentovanje|Kurentovanje}}”節中，作為豐收祭的一部分，参与者會穿着由[[绵羊|绵羊]]或[[兔子|兔子]]的毛皮制成的，带有羽毛和角的服装<ref name="LawsonRufus20142">{{cite book|last1=Lawson|first1=Kristan|last2=Rufus|first2=Anneli|title=Weird Europe: A Guide to Bizarre, Macabre, and Just Plain Weird Sights|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ua3cAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT434|accessdate=9 November 2014|date=2014-04-08|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=9781466867628|pages=434–}}</ref>。
* 1844年于[[伦敦|伦敦]]，[[費尼爾司·泰勒·巴納姆|P. T. 巴納姆]]曾让一个人穿著吃生肉的“[[猿人|猿人]]”兽装，參與[[马戏团|马戏团]]的串場表演<ref name="Weinstock20142">{{cite book|last=Weinstock|first=Professor Jeffrey|title=The Ashgate Encyclopedia of Literary and Cinematic Monsters|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=NI1zBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA45|accessdate=8 November 2014|date=2014-01-08|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=9781409425625|pages=45–}}</ref>。
* 兽装有時作为一种戏服被用于[[电影|电影]]拍摄之中<ref name="Geiger20112">{{cite book|last=Geiger|first=Jeffrey|title=American Documentary Film: Projecting the Nation|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ceHQj9ccLyIC&pg=PA61|accessdate=9 November 2014|year=2011|publisher=Edinburgh University Press|isbn=9780748621484|pages=61–}}</ref>。在[[电视连续剧|电视连续剧]]《{{link-en|大脚哈利|Harry and the Hendersons}}》中，使用的兽装道具製作花费高达100万美元<ref name="Company19912">{{cite book|last=Company|first=Johnson Publishing|title=Jet|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=KLsDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA62|accessdate=9 November 2014|date=1991-02-04|publisher=Johnson Publishing Company|pages=62–|archive-date=2016-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223064649/https://books.google.com/books?id=KLsDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA62|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
* 兽装曾和一些公共事件有關，例如目击[[大腳怪|大腳怪]]的事件<ref name="LoxtonProthero20132">{{cite book|last1=Loxton|first1=Daniel|last2=Prothero|first2=Donald R.|title=Abominable Science: Origins of the Yeti, Nessie, and other Famous Cryptids|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=kTsgAAAAQBAJ&pg=PT47|accessdate=9 November 2014|date=2013-08-13|publisher=Columbia University Press|isbn=9780231526814|pages=47–}}</ref> <ref name="Baker2">{{cite book|last=Baker|first=Robert A.|title=Missing Pieces: How to Investigate Ghosts, Ufos, Psychics, and Other Mysteries|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=ehvORpWynGYC&pg=PA259|accessdate=9 November 2014|publisher=Prometheus Books, Publishers|isbn=9781615924141|pages=259–|archive-date=2016-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161223055942/https://books.google.com/books?id=ehvORpWynGYC&pg=PA259|dead-url=no}}</ref>。
* 有一些兽迷選擇將穿著獸裝結合工作，例如扮演體育競赛中的隊伍[[吉祥物|吉祥物]]。但并不是所有的吉祥物都是动物形象，仍須配合雇主的要求扮演特定角色<ref name="fluffpiece2">{{cite news|first=Dave|last=Maass|coauthors=|title=Fluff Piece|date=2007-10-07|publisher=Santa Fe Reporter|url=http://sfreporter.com/stories/fluff_piece/1966/|work=|pages=|accessdate=2008-04-03|language=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130202051125/http://sfreporter.com/stories/fluff_piece/1966/|archivedate=2013-02-02}}</ref>。

